# Never Skip Pre-Commit Hook

**NEVER** use `--no-verify`, `-n`, or `--no-gpg-sign` (or any flag that bypasses git hooks) when committing.

- Always run the full pre-commit hook (format:check, codegen:check, lint-staged, typecheck, test)
- If the hook fails, fix the issues rather than bypassing
- The pre-commit hook exists to catch problems before they land in the repo
